# Fluff Date: 2026-02-16 11:04:06
overview:<p>The Chimera was born from an ambitious collaborative effort between the Draconis Combine, Federated Commonwealth, and Lyran Alliance in the years preceding Operations Bulldog and Serpent. Conceived in a spirit of mutual cooperation similar to the earlier Gunslinger project, the forty-ton medium BattleMech was designed to showcase the technological advances achieved by all three nations. The Lyran Alliance joined the project at the behest of Archon Katherine Steiner-Davion, whose engineers quickly came to dominate the design process after she assumed the Regency of the Federated Commonwealth. By that point, the considerable investment of time and resources by all parties left no option but to proceed, and the Chimera entered full-scale production in 3063.</p><p>Manufactured by Brigadier Corporation on Oliver, Independence Weaponry on Quentin, and Kressly Warworks on Epsilon Eridani under license, the Chimera serves as a capable light cavalry and skirmisher platform fielded across multiple successor states.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Chimera is designed to function within light and cavalry formations, delivering firepower well above what most forty-ton designs can manage while maintaining the speed to keep pace with scouting elements. Built on a Chameleon Light Endo 2 chassis powered by a GM 240 Extra Light engine, the design achieves a top speed of ninety-seven kilometers per hour, further enhanced by six Rawlings 40 jump jets providing a hundred-eighty-meter jump capability.</p><p>The armament reflects the Chimera's multinational origins. An arm-mounted ExoStar extended-range large laser provides effective engagement at long ranges, while a Shigunga MRM-20 launcher delivers devastating medium-range volleys that few medium BattleMechs can match. A BrightBloom extended-range medium laser and Scatter Gun light machine gun round out the weapons suite for close-quarters engagements. Despite the concentration of energy weapons, the Chimera manages its heat effectively under normal conditions, though aggressive pilots who push the design to its limits will encounter heat management challenges.</p><p>The Chimera's primary weakness lies in its armor protection. Carrying only seven tons of StarGuard CCM armor, the design offers protection comparable to many light BattleMechs rather than its medium-class peers. Its designers accepted this trade-off, reasoning that the 'Mech's speed, jump capability, and firepower would compensate for its thin skin.</p>

deployment:<p>Introduced in 3069, this variant represents a radical departure from the base Chimera design. The entire weapons suite is replaced with a snub-nose PPC, four medium lasers, a small laser, and a small pulse laser, while a sword mounted in the right arm provides devastating melee capability. Triple Strength Myomer amplifies the 'Mech's physical attacks when running hot, and a C3 slave unit maintains network connectivity. A larger 280-rated extra-light engine increases the cruising speed to seventy-six kilometers per hour, with TSM activation pushing the design to nearly a hundred and twenty kilometers per hour. Seven jump jets provide a two-hundred-ten-meter jump range. Produced exclusively at Kressly Warworks on Epsilon Eridani, this aggressive close-combat configuration trades the original's ranged versatility for overwhelming short-range lethality.</p>

history:<p>The Chimera's development was shaped as much by politics as by engineering. The initial joint venture between the Draconis Combine and Federated Commonwealth was intended as a diplomatic gesture in the lead-up to the campaigns against Clan Smoke Jaguar. When Archon Katherine Steiner-Davion inserted the Lyran Alliance into the project, Lyran corporations rapidly took control of the design process, transforming what had been a cooperative endeavor into something quite different from its original conception.</p><p>When the Chimera entered service in 3063, the political situation had deteriorated further. Katherine directed the full production run from Brigadier Corporation's Oliver plant and half of Independence Weaponry's Quentin output to units loyal to her faction. The first deployments went to the Alarion Jaegers, the Tenth Deneb Light Cavalry, and the Third Robinson Rangers, all formations aligned with Katherine. Coordinator Theodore Kurita, recognizing the threat this posed to balanced distribution, responded by licensing production to Kressly Warworks on Epsilon Eridani, ensuring that pro-Victor elements within the Armed Forces of the Federated Commonwealth could also acquire the design.</p><p>The C3-equipped variant quickly found its way into several Davion Guards and Crucis Lancers regiments, produced at both the Quentin and Epsilon Eridani facilities. The introduction of the more radical CMA-2K variant in 3069 demonstrated the design's adaptability, trading ranged versatility for close-combat lethality through the integration of Triple Strength Myomer and a melee weapon.</p><p>During the Jihad, all three production facilities fell under Word of Blake control, with manufacturing continuing under their direction. The Brigadier and Independence Weaponry plants ceased Chimera production in the post-Jihad era, while the Kressly Warworks facility on Epsilon Eridani transitioned through Republic of the Sphere oversight and has remained the most consistent source of new Chimeras. By the ilClan era, Epsilon Eridani had returned to Capellan Confederation control, with Kressly continuing to produce all three variants.</p>

